
@startuml

' Define classes
class Faculty {
  +name: String
  +institutes: Set<Institute>
  +dean: Employee
  +totalEmployees: int
}

class Institute {
  +name: String
  +address: String
  +researchAssistants: Set<ResearchAssistant>
}

class Employee {
  +socialSecurityNumber: String
  +name: String
  +email: String
  +type: String
}

class ResearchAssistant extends Employee {
  +fieldOfResearch: String
  +projects: Set<Project>
}

class Project {
  +name: String
  +startDate: Date
  +endDate: Date
  +hours: int
}

class Lecturer extends ResearchAssistant {
  +coursesTaught: Set<Course>
}

class Course {
  +id: String
  +name: String
  +weeklyDuration: int
}

' Associations
Faculty "1" -- "0..*" Institute : consists of
Faculty "1" -- "1" Dean : has
Institute "1" -- "0..*" ResearchAssistant : contains
ResearchAssistant "1" -- "0..*" Project : involved in
ResearchAssistant "1" -- "0..*" Lecturer : is a
Lecturer "1" -- "0..*" Course : teaches
Employee <|-- ResearchAssistant : is a type of
Employee <|-- Lecturer : is a type of

@enduml

### Notes:
- `Faculty` has a `dean`, which is an `Employee`.
- `Institute` has a name and address, and contains `ResearchAssistant`s.
- `Employee` is an abstract class with common attributes for all employees (SSN, name, email).
- `ResearchAssistant` is a subclass of `Employee` and can be involved in `Project`s.
- `Lecturer` is a subclass of `ResearchAssistant` and teaches `Course`s.
- `Course` has a unique ID, name, and weekly duration.

